  "text": "The main aims of systemic therapy in DR are to reduce the risk of diabetic patients developing these conditions in the first place and to reduce the risk of progression of existing retinopathy or maculopathy to more severe, sightthreatening forms. Systemic therapies are designed to target the key modifiable risk factors, which in the case of both DR and DME are metabolic and blood pressure control [CITATION_1] .",
